<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/829: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-14T21:00:00+01:00">August 14, 1935—9 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received August 14—5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>275. Secretary General has circulated a note from the Abyssinian
                                    Government under date of August 12th laying an “appeal” before
                                    the members of the Council in which it inquires whether the
                                    Council will remain unmoved in the face of the situation whereby
                                    the Italian Government continues sending troops to Africa with
                                    the avowed intention of attacking Abyssinia while the Abyssinian
                                    Government find it impossible to obtain means of defense outside
                                    its own frontiers being met with embargoes on arms wherever it
                                    turns.</p>
                                <p>Informed that full text has been sent by the United Press.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>